#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn47.95-104"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn47.95-104:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 47 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 47 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.95-104:0.2"
msgid "10. Oghavagga "
msgstr "10. Floods "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn47.95-104:0.3"
msgid "95–104. Uddhambhāgiyādisutta "
msgstr "95–104. Higher Fetters, Etc. "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.192, sc1
msgctxt "sn47.95-104:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, uddhambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni. "
msgstr "(To be expanded as in SN 45.171–179, with the following as the final discourse.) “Mendicants, there are five higher fetters. "

msgctxt "sn47.95-104:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "sn47.95-104:1.3"
msgid "Rūparāgo, arūparāgo, māno, uddhaccaṃ, avijjā—"
msgstr "Desire for rebirth in the realm of luminous form, desire for rebirth in the formless realm, conceit, restlessness, and ignorance. "

msgctxt "sn47.95-104:1.4"
msgid "imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañcuddhambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni. "
msgstr "These are the five higher fetters. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.95-104:1.5"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ uddhambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ abhiññāya pariññāya parikkhayāya pahānāya cattāro satipaṭṭhānā bhāvetabbā. "
msgstr "The four kinds of mindfulness meditation should be developed for the direct knowledge, complete understanding, finishing, and giving up of these five higher fetters. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn47.95-104:2.1"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn47.95-104:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ; "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn47.95-104:2.3"
msgid "vedanāsu … pe … "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings … "

msgctxt "sn47.95-104:2.4"
msgid "citte … pe … "
msgstr "mind … "

msgctxt "sn47.95-104:2.5"
msgid "dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.95-104:2.6"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ uddhambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ abhiññāya pariññāya parikkhayāya pahānāya ime cattāro satipaṭṭhānā bhāvetabbā”ti. "
msgstr "These four kinds of mindfulness meditation should be developed for the direct knowledge, complete understanding, finishing, and giving up of these five higher fetters.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.95-104:2.7"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn47.95-104:3.1"
msgid "(Yathā maggasaṃyuttaṃ tathā satipaṭṭhānasaṃyuttaṃ vitthāretabbaṃ.) "
msgstr "(The Linked Discourses on Mindfulness Meditation should be expanded as in the Linked Discourses on the Path.) "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.95-104:3.2"
msgid "Oghavaggo dasamo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn47.95-104:4.1"
msgid "Ogho yogo upādānaṃ, "
msgstr "Floods, bonds, grasping, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn47.95-104:4.2"
msgid "ganthā anusayena ca; "
msgstr "ties, and underlying tendencies, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn47.95-104:4.3"
msgid "Kāmaguṇā nīvaraṇā, "
msgstr "kinds of sensual stimulation, hindrances, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn47.95-104:4.4"
msgid "khandhā oruddhambhāgiyāti. "
msgstr "aggregates, and fetters high and low. "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn47.95-104:4.5"
msgid "Satipaṭṭhānasaṃyuttaṃ tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr "The Linked Discourses on Mindfulness Meditation is the third section."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
